But art criticism is more than just commenting on a work of art or pointing out what's wrong with it. In fact, art criticism is the act of analyzing and evaluating any type of art. More specifically, art criticism: Involves your own interpretation ; Is done to help you understand a particular work of art by using what you know of art theory, and ; Establishes where a work fits in with the different artistic styles and movements throughout art history ; Speaking of history, art criticism has been a part of many different cultures, as evaluating art has been seen as a tradition.
